addToWhitelist(address).details: Allows to add destination to whitelist. This can only be done via a Safe transaction.

changeMasterCopy(address).details: Allows to upgrade the contract. This can only be done via a Safe transaction.

executeWhitelisted(address,uint256,bytes.details: Returns if Safe transaction is to a whitelisted destination.
executeWhitelisted(address,uint256,bytes.return: Returns if transaction can be executed.

removeFromWhitelist(address).details: Allows to remove destination from whitelist. This can only be done via a Safe transaction.

setup(address[]).details: Setup function sets initial storage of contract.

devdoc.title: Whitelist Module - Allows to execute transactions to whitelisted addresses without confirmations.
